definition.value: A class of N,N-dihydroxy-alpha-amino-acids consisting of homologues of N,N-dihydroxymethionine where there is a minimum of four methylene groups between the alpha-carbon and sulfur atoms.

A 1-(alk-1Z-enyl)-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(N-acyl)ethanolamine(1-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of 1-O-(1Z-octadecenyl)-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(N-hexadecanoyl)ethanolamine; major species at pH 7.3.

A 1-(alk-1Z-enyl)-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(N-acyl)ethanolamine(1-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of 1-(1Z-octadecenyl)-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(N-oleoyl)ethanolamine; major species at pH 7.3.
A docosanoid that is (8E,10Z,14E,16Z,18E)-docosapentaenoic acid carrying three hydroxy substituents at positions 7, 13 and 20.
A beta-diketone obtained by formal oxidation of the 2 and 4 hydroxy groups of scyllo-inositol to the corresponding ketones.

A 1-(alk-1Z-enyl)-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(N-acyl)ethanolamine(1-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of 1-(1Z-octadecenyl)-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(N-arachidonoyl)ethanolamine; major species at pH 7.3.
A 1-(Z)-alk-1-enyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of any 1-(1Z-octadecenyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
A docosanoid that is (8Z,10E,14E,16Z,19Z)-docosapentaenoic acid carrying three hydroxy substituents at positions 7, 12 and 13.
A docosanoid that is (9E,11E,14E,16Z,19Z)-docosapentaenoic acid carrying three hydroxy substituents at positions 7, 8 and 13.
A docosanoid that is (8E,10Z,14E,16Z,19Z)-docosapentaenoic acid carrying two hydroxy substituents at positions 7 and 13.
A 5(),6(S)-epoxy-18-hydroxy-(7E,9E,11Z,14Z,16E)-icosapentaenoic acid in which the 18-hydroxy group has S-configuration.
An N-hydroxy-L-polyhomomethionine in which there are four methylene groups between the alpha-carbon and sulfur atoms.
An N-hydroxy-L-polyhomomethionine in which there are five methylene groups between the alpha-carbon and sulfur atoms.
An N-hydroxy-L-polyhomomethionine in which there are six methylene groups between the alpha-carbon and sulfur atoms.
An N-hydroxy-L-polyhomomethionine in which there are seven methylene groups between the alpha-carbon and sulfur atoms.
An N-hydroxy-L-polyhomomethionine in which there are eight methylene groups between the alpha-carbon and sulfur atoms.
An N,N-dihydroxy-L-polyhomomethionine in which there are four methylene groups between the alpha-carbon and sulfur atoms.
An N,N-dihydroxy-L-polyhomomethionine in which there are five methylene groups between the alpha-carbon and sulfur atoms.
An N,N-dihydroxy-L-polyhomomethionine in which there are six methylene groups between the alpha-carbon and sulfur atoms.
An N,N-dihydroxy-L-polyhomomethionine in which there are seven methylene groups between the alpha-carbon and sulfur atoms.
An androstanoid that is 5alpha-dihydrotestosterone carrying an additional hydroxy susbstituent at position 19.
An androstanoid that is 5alpha-dihydrotestosterone carrying an additional oxo susbstituent at position 19.
An N,N-dihydroxy-L-polyhomomethionine in which there are eight methylene groups between the alpha-carbon and sulfur atoms.
A member of the class of resolvins that is (6E,8Z,11Z,14Z,16E)-icosapentaenoic acid carrying two hydroxy substituents at positions 5 and 18 (the 5S,18S stereoisomer).
A deoxyribonucleotide residue derived from cyclobutane pyrimidine dimer 5'-phosphate.
An androstanoid that is 5alpha-dihydrotestosterone carrying an additional hydroxy susbstituent at position 18.
A resolvin that is (6Z,8E,10E,14Z,16E)-icosa-6,8,10,14,16-pentaenoic acid which is substituted at positions 5, 12 and 18 by hydroxy groups (the 5S,12R,18S stereoisomer).
An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 8,9-epoxy-(5Z,11Z,14Z)-icosatrienoic acid.
A fatty acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of any short-chain fatty acyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
The monoprotonated form of quinine, the predominant species at pH7.3.
An L-isoleucine derivative resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of (+)-7-isojasmonic acid with the amino group of L-isoleucine.
An L-isoleucine derivative resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of (+)-12-hydroxy-7-isojasmonic acid with the amino group of L-isoleucine.
A tripeptide consisting of Z-Val-Ala-Asp(OMe) in which the C-terminal OH group has been replaced by a fluoromethyl group. An irreversible pan-caspase inhibitor.
A 3-oxo-Delta(4) steroid that is progesterone substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 6, 16 and 17 (6beta,16alpha,17alpha-stereoisomer).
An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 11,12-epoxy-(5Z,8Z,14Z)-icosatrienoic acid.
Tripeptide fragment from a polypeptide where Zaa is neither Pro nor hydroxyproline
A pregnane sterol that is pregnenolone substituted by two hydroxy groups at positions 16 and 17 (16alpha,17alpha-stereoisomer).
A 3-oxo monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of acetoacetic acid, arising from deprotonation of the carboxy group.
An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 14,15-epoxy-(5Z,8Z,11Z)-icosatrienoic acid.
A cholestanoid that is desmosterol carrying an additional hydroxy susbstituent at position 26.
A cholestanoid that is 7-dehydrocholesterol carrying an additional hydroxy substituent at position 25.
